<HEAD>Baby Ostrich Not Awed by Pauley</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Pauley-Today, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shortly after Jane Pauley of ``Today'' told
millions of viewers Friday she's leaving NBC's show, she learned
anew what the show's first host, Dave Garroway, learned early on _
that animals are unpredictable.
   Garroway had to put up with star chimp J. Fred Muggs. Pauley had
to put up with a baby ostrich. The guest bird, which she held
during a discussion of such creatures, soiled Pauley's skirt.
   Asked after the show if she considered this a bad omen, Pauley
laughed and replied, in mock dismay: ``I consider it humbling and
altogether uncalled for.''
